title: Counties won by Clinton in the Florida Democratic primary, United States, Jan 29, 2008
name: Counties won by Clinton in the Florida Democratic primary, United States, Jan 29, 2008
description: The original data for the map is from Florida's Dept. of Elections website http://enight.dos.state.fl.us/ posted as of 4:51 AM on 30th January, 2008.        The share of votes for Clinton, Obama and Edwards were computed along with the difference in share of votes between the top two contender, namely Clinton and Obama.              Even though Clinton won by nearly 50% (~854,000) to Obama's 33%  (567,000          ) and Edwards 14.5% (248,000), none of them will get any delegates since Democratic National Committee stripped Florida of all its delegates for moving its primary before the Super Tuesday primaries/caucuses.  That should not diminish the importance of the vote since more than 1.5 million votes were cast in the Democratic primary, that is more than the combined votes cast in Iowa, New Hampshire and South Carolina.              Clinton won most of his votes in Middle and Southern part of the state while Obama and Edwards won mostly in the North, North-East and North-West counties of the state.  Look for data and maps on GeoCommons that show which counties were won by which candidates.
